The Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem tells us that for a linear functional `L : C‚āÄ(X) ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ`, there exists a unique measure `őľ` such that `LŌÜ = ‚ąę ŌÜ dőľ`. The norm of the linear functional is equal to the total variation of the measure: `‚ÄĖL‚ÄĖ = őľ.variation Set.univ`.

