The proof strategy is to:
1.  Express the integral of `f` against `E_{a, x,y}` as the value of the linear functional `g ‚Ü¶ ‚ü®x, g(a)y‚ü©_‚Ąā` evaluated at `f`. This is done by `h1`.
2.  Use the bound `‚ÄĖ‚ü®x, g(a)y‚ü©_‚Ąā‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖg‚ÄĖ` (derived from `cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound`) to show `‚ÄĖ‚ü®x, (cfcHom ha.isStarNormal f)y‚ü©_‚Ąā‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ`. This is done by `h3`.
3.  Show `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` using the hypothesis `hf_bounded : ‚ąÄ x, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C`. This is done by `h4`.
4.  Combine the inequalities to get `‚ÄĖ‚ü®x, (cfcHom ha.isStarNormal f)y‚ü©_‚Ąā‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * C`. This is done by `h2`.
5.  The main goal is `‚ÄĖ(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).integral f‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * C`, which follows from `h1` and `h2`.

