  have h_le : ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a) ‚Č§ C := by
    apply ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup_le
    intro x hx
    have hfx : ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C := hf_bounded x
    simpa using hfx
```

For the reverse inequality, we need to show that `C ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`. By definition of `essSup`, we need to show that for any `őĶ > 0`, there is a set `S` of measure `‚Č• 0` such that `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č• C - őĶ` for all `x ‚ąą S`. But since `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` everywhere, we can take `S = ‚ąÖ`, which has measure `0`. Then `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č• C - őĶ` is trivially true for all `x ‚ąą ‚ąÖ`.

```tactics
