  have h1 : ‚ąÄ x, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C := by
    intro x
    apply hf_bounded x
```

To show `C ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`, we use the fact that `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)` is the infimum of the set of upper bounds for `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ`. Since `C` is an upper bound (as shown by `h1`), `C` must be greater than or equal to the infimum.

```tactics
