  have h3 : ‚ąÄ x, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C := h1
```

We need to show that `C ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`. By definition, `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a) = inf { M : ‚ĄĚ | ‚ąÄ x, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ M }`. Since `C` is in this set (as shown by `h3`), `C ‚Č• ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)` is false. We need `C ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`.

Let's correct this. To show `C ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`, we need to show that `C` is a lower bound for the set of upper bounds. But `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)` is the infimum of the set of upper bounds. So we need to show that `C ‚Č• ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ.essSup (spectrum ‚Ąā a)`. This is not what we want.

