First, we know from `cfc_toComplexMeasure_bounded` that `‚ÄĖ(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).integral f‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ`. Since `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` for all `x`, we have `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` (as the supremum of `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ` is ‚Č§ `C`).

So we need to show that `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C`. The hypothesis `hf_bounded` gives us `‚ąÄ x, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C`. To show `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` (where `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ` is the operator norm of `f` as a function from `‚ÜĎ(spectrum ‚Ąā a)` to `‚Ąā`), we need to show that `sup ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C`.

But `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ` (as a function) is the supremum of `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ` over all `x` in the domain. Since `hf_bounded` gives `‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C` for all `x`, the supremum is ‚Č§ `C`. So `‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ C`.

Then, using `cfc_toComplexMeasure_bounded`, we have `‚ÄĖ(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).integral f‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖx‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖy‚ÄĖ * C`.

